HEADWORD: Limu
<hw>Li"mu</hw> <pr>(l⟦emac⟧"m⟦oomac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The Hawaiian name for seaweeds. Over sixty kinds
are used as food, and have species names, as <spn>Limu Lipoa</spn>,
<spn>Limu palawai</spn>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

